"""Opening database — a curated list of 500+ common chess openings.

Each entry is ``(ECO_code, opening_name, [UCI_moves...])`` where *UCI_moves*
is the sequence of moves that defines the opening in UCI format (e.g.
``"e2e4"``).

The list is sorted roughly by ECO code (A00 → E99).  It is imported by
``openings.py`` which builds the lookup tree and provides the public
``detect_opening()`` and ``get_opening_continuations()`` APIs.

Entries with the same ECO code represent different sub-variations of the
same classification.
"""

from __future__ import annotations

